## Phase 2: Play JSON Migration (2.9.2 → 3.0.6)

**⚠️ Breaking Change:** Play JSON 3.0.x changed group ID and has stricter implicit resolution.

### Step 1: Update Play JSON Dependencies

**Location:** `project/Dependencies.scala` or `project/LibsPool.scala`

```scala
// Before (Play JSON 2.9.2)
val playJson = "com.typesafe.play" %% "play-json" % "2.9.2"
val playJsonJoda = "com.typesafe.play" %% "play-json-joda" % "2.9.2"

// After (Play JSON 3.0.6)
val playJson = "org.playframework" %% "play-json" % "3.0.6"
val playJsonJoda = "org.playframework" %% "play-json-joda" % "3.0.6"
```

### Step 2: Update play-json-extensions

**⚠️ Critical:** `ai.x:play-json-extensions` is incompatible with Scala 2.13.18. Use Guardian fork.

**Location:** `project/Dependencies.scala`

```scala
// Before
val playJsonExtensions = "ai.x" %% "play-json-extensions" % "0.42.0"

// After (Guardian fork)
val playJsonExtensions = "com.gu" %% "play-json-extensions" % "1.0.4"
```

### Step 3: Update Imports

**Mass replace across all Scala files:**

```bash
# Find files using old imports
find . -name "*.scala" -type f -exec grep -l "import ai.x.play.json" {} \;

# Replace with Guardian fork
find . -name "*.scala" -type f -exec sed -i '' 's/import ai\.x\.play\.json/import com.gu.ai.x.play.json/g' {} \;
```

**Before:**
```scala
import ai.x.play.json.Jsonx
import ai.x.play.json.Encoders._
```

**After:**
```scala
import com.gu.ai.x.play.json.Jsonx
import com.gu.ai.x.play.json.Encoders._
```

### Step 4: Add Global Dependency Overrides and Exclusions

**Location:** `build.sbt`

```scala
// Force Play JSON 3.0.6 (org.playframework) and exclude old com.typesafe.play versions globally
ThisBuild / dependencyOverrides ++= Seq(
  "org.playframework" %% "play-json" % "3.0.6",
  "org.playframework" %% "play-functional" % "3.0.6",
  "org.playframework" %% "play-json-joda" % "3.0.6"
)

ThisBuild / excludeDependencies ++= Seq(
  ExclusionRule(organization = "com.typesafe.play", name = "play-json"),
  ExclusionRule(organization = "com.typesafe.play", name = "play-functional"),
  ExclusionRule(organization = "com.typesafe.play", name = "play-json-joda"),
  ExclusionRule(organization = "ai.x", name = "play-json-extensions")  // Exclude old ai.x version
)
```

### Step 5: Handle Assembly Merge Strategy (for sbt-assembly)

**Location:** `project/DependenciesMisc.scala` or similar

```scala
import sbtassembly.AssemblyUtils
import sbtassembly.MergeStrategy

object PlayJson {
  /** Prefers org.playframework version over com.typesafe.play version for Play JSON conflicts */
  val preferNewVersion: MergeStrategy = new MergeStrategy {
    val name = "preferNewPlayJson"
    def apply(tempDir: File, path: String, files: Seq[File]): Either[String, Seq[(File, String)]] = {
      val sortedFiles = files.sortBy { f =>
        val (jar, _, _, isJar) = AssemblyUtils.sourceOfFileForMerge(tempDir, f)
        if (isJar) {
          val jarName = jar.getName
          if (jarName.contains("org.playframework")) { 0 }
          else if (jarName.contains("com.typesafe.play")) { 1 }
          else { 2 }
        } else { 2 }
      }
      Right(Seq(sortedFiles.head -> path))
    }
  }
}

mergeStrategy := {
  case PathList("play", "api", "libs", _*) => PlayJson.preferNewVersion
  case x => (mergeStrategy.value)(x)
}
```

